<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-12-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-12-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="581" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d581">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Ambassador <persName type="to">Reid</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-12-04"><hi rend="italic">December 4,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Department is informed by Alexander that he has heard reports of one
                            American vessel fishing on Sunday. Department will advise Mr. Reid if
                            report is found to be true. In the meantime strictest injunction has
                            been repeated against any such fishing.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>